### Configure Routing Middleware runtime with Node.js or Edge

Source: https://vercel.com/docs/routing-middleware

Export a config object with runtime property set to 'nodejs' or 'edge' (default) in middleware files. The middleware function receives a Request object and returns a Response. This configuration works across Next.js App Router, Next.js Pages Router, and other frameworks.

```typescript
export const config = {
  runtime: 'nodejs', // or 'edge' (default)
};
export default function middleware(request: Request) {
  // Your middleware logic here
  return new Response('Hello from your Middleware!');
}
```

```javascript
export const config = {
  runtime: 'nodejs' // or 'edge' (default)
}
export default function middleware(request: Request) {
  // Your middleware logic here
  return new Response('Hello from your Middleware!');
}
```

