### Implement Dynamic Rewrites with Edge Config in Next.js Middleware (TypeScript)

Source: https://vercel.com/docs/incremental-migration

This TypeScript code demonstrates a Next.js middleware function that utilizes Vercel's Edge Config to perform dynamic URL rewrites. It fetches rewrite rules from Edge Config, allowing for real-time changes without redeploying the application. The middleware intercepts incoming requests and, if a matching rewrite rule is found, modifies the URL and serves the content from the new destination, ensuring immediate application of routing changes.

```typescript
import { get } from '@vercel/edge-config';
import { NextRequest, NextResponse } from 'next/server';

export const config = {
  matcher: '/((?!api|_next/static|favicon.ico).*)',
};

export default async function middleware(request: NextRequest) {
  const url = request.nextUrl;
  const rewrites = await get('rewrites'); // Get rewrites stored in Edge Config

  for (const rewrite of rewrites) {
    if (rewrite.source === url.pathname) {
      url.pathname = rewrite.destination;
      return NextResponse.rewrite(url);
    }
  }

  return NextResponse.next();
}
```

