### Create Next.js Middleware to Read Vercel Edge Config

Source: https://vercel.com/docs/edge-config/get-started

These code snippets demonstrate creating a Next.js middleware (`middleware.ts` or `middleware.js`) to read a 'greeting' value from the Vercel Edge Config store. The middleware intercepts requests to the `/welcome` path and responds with the retrieved value using `NextResponse.json`.

```ts
import { NextResponse } from 'next/server';
import { get } from '@vercel/edge-config';

export const config = { matcher: '/welcome' };

export async function middleware() {
  const greeting = await get('greeting');
  return NextResponse.json(greeting);
}
```

```js
import { NextResponse } from 'next/server';
import { get } from '@vercel/edge-config';

export const config = { matcher: '/welcome' };

export async function middleware() {
  const greeting = await get('greeting');
  return NextResponse.json(greeting);
}
```

