### Configure Vercel Function for Edge Runtime with TypeScript

Source: https://vercel.com/docs/functions/runtimes/edge-runtime

This snippet demonstrates how to configure a Vercel Function to run on the Edge runtime using TypeScript. By setting `export const runtime = 'edge'`, the function will execute in a lightweight Edge environment. It also defines a basic GET request handler returning a simple response.

```TypeScript
export const runtime = 'edge'; // 'nodejs' is the default

export function GET(request: Request) {
  return new Response(`I am an Vercel Function!`, {
    status: 200,
  });
}
```

