This Next.js Edge Middleware example demonstrates how to create an emergency fallback mechanism using Vercel Edge Config. It retrieves a boolean variable, 'isNewVersionActive', from Edge Config to conditionally rewrite requests to a legacy server path, enabling instant rollbacks without redeploying code. This is useful for managing unexpected issues with new features.

```typescript
import { NextRequest, NextResponse } from 'next/server';
import { get } from '@vercel/edge-config';

export const config = {
  matcher: ['/'], // URL to match
