### POST /v1/edge-config

Source: https://vercel.com/docs/llms-full

Create a new Edge Config. This endpoint allows you to set up a new configuration resource that can store key-value pairs accessible from edge functions.

```APIDOC
## POST /v1/edge-config

### Description
Create a new Edge Config resource.

### Method
POST

### Endpoint
/v1/edge-config

### Request Body
- **name** (string) - Required - The name of the Edge Config
- **items** (object) - Optional - Initial key-value pairs to populate the config

### Request Example
{
  "name": "my-edge-config",
  "items": {
    "key1": "value1",
    "key2": "value2"
  }
}

### Response
#### Success Response (201)
- **id** (string) - The newly created Edge Config ID
- **name** (string) - The name of the Edge Config
- **createdAt** (string) - Timestamp of creation

### Response Example
{
  "id": "ecfg_xxx",
  "name": "my-edge-config",
  "createdAt": "2024-01-15T10:30:00Z"
}
```

